 a health monitoring system that allows users to track their body vitals such as blood pressure, sugar level, and heartbeat, and send the data remotely to healthcare professionals, you will need a combination of hardware components, sensors, and software. 

Components needed:
1. Arduino board (e.g., Arduino Uno)
2. Vital signs sensors (e.g., blood pressure sensor, glucose sensor, heart rate sensor)
3. Wireless module (e.g., Wi-Fi or Bluetooth module)
4. Display module (e.g., LCD display)
5. Power source (e.g., battery or power adapter)
6. Breadboard and jumper wires

 Arduino code:


arduino
